12th Street, east side, north from 27th Avenue, showing a row of fashionable homes. The corner house is a Blackwell house, having been owned by R. M. Blackwell in 1873. The other homes were the property of C. R. Trafford. 12th Street was formerly Remsen Street.

P. L. Sperr

June 2, 1927

12th Street, east side, north from 27th Avenue, showing a row of private homes of a type most fashionable at the turn of the century. The first house was owned by a member of the Blackwell family, View 2 shows the Blackwell house.

P. L. Sperr

March 11, 1931
Views 1,2:

12th Street, east side, north from 27th Avenue, showing a row of private homes of a type most fashionable at the turn of the century. The first house was owned by a member of the Blackwell family, View 2 shows the Blackwell house.

P. L. Sperr

March 11, 1931
Views 1,2:

27th Avenue, at, and adjoining the N. W. (corner of 12th Street. The corner house was built by Dr. Taylor (according to P. L. Sperr) about a century ago and has always been occupied by men of the same profession.

View 1: P. L. Sperr

View 2: George D. Chinn
